# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenClaw — what NEVER enters git.
#
# Design: agent CODE + PERSONA are committed; runtime DATA / STATE / SECRETS
# stay on disk (the bots read them at runtime) but are excluded here.
# A fresh clone is reconfigured from the committed *.example.json templates.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Node deps ──
node_modules/
**/node_modules/

# ── Per-agent runtime config (group_ids, sheet_ids, webhooks, drive ids) ──
# The bot reads these at runtime. Commit *.example.json instead.
**/.config/*.json
!**/.config/*.example.json

# ── Gateway / workspace state ──
**/.openclaw/
**/.openclaw-cli-images/
**/.claude/
*-state.json
**/workspace-state.json
**/source-origin.json

# ── Runtime data trees (chat logs, runs, lessons, ledgers, rosters, telemetry) ──
# covers chat-log/**, runs/**, lessons/**, self-edit/**, cases/**, players.json,
# sessions.json, last-inbound.json, roster.md, watchdog/session-hygiene markers.
**/data/

# ── Real-estate deal documents (signed contracts, bank letters, PDFs) ──
**/deal-data/

# ── Per-person PII tree (CVs, profiles, cv-summary, sent-suggestions, *-state) ──
**/people/

# ── Dated/daily memory notes — NOT the curated MEMORY.md at a workspace root ──
**/memory/

# ── Inbound media cache (real photos, gov docs, customer images) ──
**/media/inbound/

# ── Backups (full PII snapshots) ──
**/.backups/

# ── Conversational-continuity mirror (verbatim recent chat) ──
**/RECENT_CHAT.md

# ── Logs / locks / OS cruft ──
*.log
*.lock
.DS_Store

# ── Safety re-includes: persona/doc files broad rules must never catch ──
!**/AGENTS.md
!**/SOUL.md
!**/IDENTITY.md
!**/USER.md
!**/TOOLS.md
!**/HEARTBEAT.md
!**/CLAUDE.md
!**/MEMORY.md
!**/BOOTSTRAP.md
!**/ACTIVATION.md
!**/HOOK.md
